<TEXT>
a woman accused of killing a psychiatric 
social worker at a hospital feb 16 was ruled incompetent to stand 
trial thursday 
allegheny county judge robert dauer ordered 31yearold edith 
anderson committed to mayview state hospital for at least 90 days 
after the director of the countys behavior clinic diagnosed her a 
paranoid schizophrenic 
ms anderson who has a 13year history of mental problems is 
charged with shooting linda rosen 27 at st francis medical 
center and holding three people hostage for about 90 minutes before 
surrendering 
the woman shouted angrily during thursdays hearing about being 
sent to mayview in three months the judge will decide whether she 
is fit to stand trial 
earlier this week ms anderson told the pittsburgh postgazette 
she shot ms rosen after becoming angry at the thought that the 
mental health system that once forced her to take drugs was now 
keeping them from her 
after running out of drugs that controlled her schizophrenia 
she had problems obtaining more medication because her welfare 
prescription card had expired she said 
she said that when she carried a handgun into the hospital i 
felt i got the power tonight i am the one i was in charge 
like i probably will never be again 
hours before the slaying a mental health counselor at braddock 
general hospital started the process of committing her to a mental 
hospital after she said i feel it makes sense to kill 
authorities said 
but before the counselor could complete the commitment ms 
anderson abruptly left the hospital 
