former president jimmy carter says he and his 
family would be in danger if secret service protection stopped 
under legislation that a senator says would end the era of the 
imperial former presidency 
elimination of security would make it almost impossible for us 
to live a normal private life at home free of uninvited visitors 
to attend major events if our attendance is publicized or to 
travel to many places in our country or abroad carter said in a 
letter to sen lawton chiles dfla 
he said there were frequent occasions when people have come to 
his hometown of plains ga and threatened him or his family with 
bodily harm 
last fall he said there were three such incidents within a 
month in one case he continued the visitor shattered the large 
glass reflector mirrors and tried to destroy the gate leading to 
his driveway 
there is no way to anticipate when one of them could be 
serious wrote carter 
carters letter and letters from former presidents gerald r 
ford and richard m nixon were made public thursday in a hearing by 
chiles senate government operations subcommittee 
ford said he can do without the federal protection and nixon 
gave up his government security in 1985 
chiles and 14 others have sponsored legislation that would end 
secret service protection of former presidents and their families 
five years after they leave office the bill also would place a 
limit on their office and staff expenses and would phase out 
funding entirely after 10 years 
secret service protection could be extended beyond the fiveyear 
period if the treasury secretary demonstrated a need for continued 
protection 
the american people want former presidents to live a dignified 
retired life as an elder statesman free from any real danger one 
free from the need to commercialize to huckster the office of 
the presidency chiles said but the programs were left 
openended things have gotten out of hand 
he said secret service protection for ford and carter and their 
families cost 8 million in 1986 in nixons last year of 1985 
federal protection cost some 3 million for him 
ford told chiles that he favored enactment of the legislation a 
nixon aide john h taylor said nixon voluntarily gave up the 
lifetime federal protection in august 1985 and mrs nixon did so in 
1984 thus saving the government 3 million annually he believed 
it was no longer appropriate for the taxpayers to bear the cost of 
his security wrote taylor 
michael endicott a secret service agent for 20 years who now is 
in charge of security for nixon said secret service protection 
often limits the recipients freedom of movement he said he has 
never felt nixons safety has been threatened since he began to 
handle his security traveling to cities around the world and 
attending sporting and other public events 
at most of these events we usually sit in the general public 
seats even though vip boxes are usually available he said 
there is more privacy with fewer people we are able to go to 
more ball games now than when he had secret service protection 
the big difference he said is that the secret service must 
protect against the potential threat while i can protect from 
the actual threat 
endicott said he believes there should be a time limit on the 
secret service protection but feels that the federal government 
should continue to be responsible for their protection 
i believe the government should provide funding to the former 
president so that they can manage their own daytoday security 
he said 
carter asked that an adequate level of security be 
continued however he said he would not object if secret service 
experts could reduce the level and cost of his protection 
there is a need for a security or law enforcement presence 
around a former president that naturally flows from occupying the 
most important office in the country he said to finance ones 
own security force however modest is a very expensive matter 
though some of our former highlevel officials have chosen to do 
so 
