<TEXT>
the commerce department turns 75 today just 
four years older than the man who runs it c william verity and 
verity claims to be a late bloomer just like the oncestaid 
agency he heads 
even as a late bloomer you can come into the scene and be a 
player verity said in an interview in his ballroomsize office 
built in the late 1920s to the specifications of one of the early 
commerce secretaries herbert hoover 
the oldest cabinet member at 71 the retired chairman of armco 
steel is still five years younger than his boss in the white house 
verity arrived on the scene in october about the time topechelon 
members of the administration plan their returns to the private 
sector 
still veritys brief tenure has been marked by activism and 
some measure of controversy 
there have been trade skirmishes with japan turf squabbles with 
other agencies and resignations of several top officials veritys 
outspoken advocacy of closer economic ties with the soviet union 
has drawn criticism from both conservatives in congress and from 
some jewish organizations 
the agency has come a long way from its creation in 1913 when 
its main functions included counting the population inspecting 
steamboats and maintaining lighthouses 
today the department enforces us trade policy probably its 
most vital role in a day of 170 billion trade deficits it also 
collects and analyzes economic data and serves as home for the 
census bureau the national weather service the bureau of 
standards and a host of other agencies 
it serves now as in the past as the business communitys 
advocate within the halls of government 
verity had retired in 1982 as chairman and chief executive 
officer of armco then based in ohio the retirement ended when he 
was picked by president reagan to head the sprawling agency after 
the death last summer of malcolm baldrige who had been commerce 
secretary since 1981 
baldrige who was extremely popular with the agencys 38000 
employes and members of congress died in a freak rodeo accident 
although under baldrige the commerce department had been the 
lead federal agency on dealing with congress on trade legislation 
verity has moved into other areas and pressed ahead with his own 
pet projects 
one has been more fully automating the departments many 
activities another was pressing for commercializaton of space an 
effort verity said gave him a quick lesson in heading a government 
agency since it brought him into conflict with the national 
aeronautics and space administration 
nasa doesnt want anybody else out there he said 
i think you find out youre not in charge he said there 
are a lot of people who have a piece of the action who have to get 
on board the mission in private business is to get something done 
in government its to move toward solving a problem but to get 
everybody on board with you as you try to solve it 
and that just requires a lot of time and a lot of massaging of 
peoples feelings and testing this and testing that 
he said his present priority is a program to help smaller 
companies export more 
i think our economy is going to be exportdriven this year 
he said our department feels we should do whatever we can to 
encourage small and medium sized companies to get into the export 
game 
his nononsense approach particularly his tough stance toward 
japan has won him a lot of fans in the business community just a 
few days on the job verity threatened japan with retaliation if it 
didnt do more to open its markets or adjust its prices to match 
the lower dollar 
while japanese officials protested the tough talk from a man 
who speaks softly and slowly won him fans among us industries 
battered by japanese imports 
other secretaries and other us spokesmen have not been 
urging the government to start speaking in plain language to these 
guys the japanese said richard muller a washington 
representative for chrysler corp 
verity also delighted conservationists by recommending sanctions 
against japan last month for the killing of minke whales in 
violation of international whaling regulations 
but sighed verity i never had any idea i would be in charge 
of whales some day and i had no idea it would take so much of my 
time 
