million a year discount on oil purchases but says he didnt take 
the idea seriously and didnt inform other government officials 
peres denies that rappaport proposed paying part of the money to 
the labor party 
the pipeline to have been constructed by san franciscobased 
bechtel group inc was never built 
mckay is investigating whether meese may have violated the 
foreign corrupt practices act which makes it a crime for us 
citizens companies or their agents to bribe foreign officials for 
help in business matters and authorizes the attorney general to 
file suit to block such practices meese says he doesnt recall 
reading the portion of wallachs memo pertaining to labor party 
payments 
