<TEXT>
physicians must be more aware of selfdestructive 
impulses in aids patients who are much more likely to commit 
suicide than the general population and even victims of other 
terminal illnesses a new study says 
the study published in todays journal of the american medical 
association found that the risk of suicide among men 20 to 59 
years old with aids was 36 times greater than for other men in that 
age group and 66 times greater than for the general population 
other studies have shown that cancer victims are up to four 
times more likely than the general population to kill themselves 
while suicide is statistically rare the study found that the 
threat to aids victims comes first when they learn they have the 
disease then again when it begins to affect the central nervous 
system 
the acquired immunodeficiency syndrome has been associated 
with secondary depression and other psychiatric syndromes all 
of which are associated with higher suicide rates the 
researchers wrote 
the lesson is that physicians treating aids patients must be 
aware of the possibility of suicide said one of the researchers 
dr peter m marzuk of cornell university medical college 
physicians should evaluate suicide risk in these patients 
carefully he said because of the risk for suicide the 
presence of concomitant psychiatric syndromes especially 
depression and delirium should lead to early psychiatric 
intervention 
an accompanying editorial emphasized the potential suicide risk 
for people who test positive for the aids virus even though some 
of them might not have the disease 
the presence of aids antibodies in a persons blood does not 
mean he has the disease but only that the virus that causes aids 
has entered his system and provoked a natural diseasefighting 
response 
the risk of suicide is one more reason that such tests should 
never be considered as routine dr richard m glass an 
associate professor of psychiatry at the university of chicago 
hospital wrote in the editorial the enormity of this problem is 
indicated by estimates that approximately 15 million americans 
have hiv antibodies 
there were reports last spring of seven suicides in the miami 
area among people who had tested positive 
roger lane hotline coordinator for miamis health crisis 
network said in a telephone interview thursday that others tried 
unsuccessfully to take their own lives on the basis of very 
preliminary tests 
the suicide outbreak coincided with the opening of new 
aidstesting centers many of which offered no counseling and some 
of which merely gave test results over the telephone he said 
if you were notifying someone they had terminal cancer you 
wouldnt do that over the phone he said 
doctors must specifically ask patients about any suicidal 
feelings glass said 
the study reported in jama focused on suicides in 1985 in new 
york city where aids is the leading cause of death of men in their 
30s there were 3828 people who had aids in the city then of whom 
12 were known to have killed themselves 
these are conservative estimates of the number of 
suicides marzuk said we dont know how many people may have 
taken an overdose of heroin for example these would never have 
been counted as suicides 
aids destroys the bodys defenses against disease leaving a 
person prey to lifethreatening infections and certain cancers 
</TEXT>
