foreign affairs committee there was no mention of the drug 
allegations before their votes 
about 14000 people live on the eight permanently inhabited 
islands of palau which comprises more than 200 islands in the 
caroline chain most of the inhabitants live in koror the capital 
some 4450 miles southwest of honolulu and 720 miles south of guam 
in a letter last october to de lugo dea administrator john lawn 
said it appears that palaus primary involvement in international 
drug trafficking is as a transshipment point for southeast asian 
heroin being smuggled to the united states 
lawn said marijuana is grown freely throughout palau and 
that there may be more than 400 heroin addicts in palau far 
higher than the percentage of addicts in the united states 
hills said palau with help requested from the dea and interior 
and state departments is trying to combat the problem he said 
that 25 marijuana and heroin suspects were arrested in a major 
bust tuesday in palau 
about the accusation that senior officials could be involved 
with heroin smuggling hills said the issue of whos involved is 
not going to be commented on because its under investigation by 
the government of palau 
he said congress should move to sever the trusteeship because 
palauan independence and increased us aid would give the islands 
government more resources to combat its problems 
