<TEXT>
the nuclear regulatory commission indicated 
friday that the tennessee valley authority may win permission 
within two weeks to restart its first nuclear reactor since its 
entire atomic power system was closed in 1985 
the commission heard its staff present a generally glowing 
report about tvas readiness to reopen the sequoyah unit 2 plant 
near chattanooga tenn after a monthlong nonnuclear heatup of 
the facility 
but i do not believe that sequoyah is ready to go critical 
yet nrc executive director victor stello said that may come 
next week or the following week 
the longpostponed restart of the sequoyah plant would mark a 
significant breakthrough for the tva nuclear system in its long 
costly journey to recover from management and safety breakdowns 
which branded it one of the worst in the history of atomic power 
its five operating reactors two at sequoyah and three at 
browns ferry near athens ga were ordered shut down in 1985 
plans for eight other plants were canceled and construction on 
four others was delayed for years 
the commission heard a lengthy presentation from tvas new 
chairman marvin j runyon and its nuclear chief steven a white 
and found little to quarrel with about tvas latest efforts to put 
the program back on track 
we truly are ready to resume the production of nuclear 
power white said we will be cautious we will be conservative 
we will be deliberate 
i did not want to apply industry standards to the tva white 
said i wanted to apply the highest standards and thats what we 
did 
representatives of the nrcs special task force for the tva 
agreed that most problems confronting a sequoyah restart have been 
resolved including major concerns about the durability of 
rubberinsulated cables and the reliability of emergency diesel 
generators necessary for power in the event of a reactor accident 
but stewart ebneter who head the task force said some concern 
remains about allegations raised in january by a previous tva 
employee after interviewing the man twice ebneter said the nrc 
staff is pursuing whether a fire hazard may be posed by the 
possiblity of cabletocable shorts a separate issue than the 
earlier problem with the siliconeinsulated cables 
ebneter said he expected to receive new technical data from the 
tva on the issue and expressed hope it would be resolved before 
the commissions next formal meeting tentatively set for march 10 
to consider a sequoyah restart 
the commission also is known to be reviewing findings of its 
office of investigation over allegations that tvas white 
