<TEXT>
improvements in the nations efficiency in 
churning out goods and services slowed by almost half last year 
despite revised figures showing higher output in the the fourth 
quarter the government said 
the labor department said thursday that productivity among 
nonfarm businesses responsible for threefourths of the nations 
economic activity rose at an annual rate of 03 percent in the 
fourth quarter in contrast to a deterioration of 02 percent 
reported in preliminary figures last month 
the revisions raised the productivity improvement for the entire 
year from 08 percent to 09 percent slightly more than half the 
16 percent gain of 1986 despite the lowest hourly labor cost 
increases in more than four decades 
</TEXT>
