otis spunkmeyer inc is wagering a 
few million cookies that it has goodyear outblimped when it comes 
to midair advertising 
the gourmet baking company embarks today on a sky tours business 
featuring a vintage 1945 dc3 hoping to capture the romance of 
aviations golden era along with the hearts and wallets of 
wellheeled customers 
kenneth rawlings chairman and chief executive officer of otis 
spunkmeyer sees the tour business as a cantmiss proposition 
even if planefuls of customers dont line up for hourlong flights 
at 75 a pop or 1200 to charter the entire 18seat aircraft 
the promotional value is high 
we look at it as our goodyear blimp rawlings said noting 
that a 95footlong sign bearing the companys name under the wing 
should grab the attention of groundbound consumers 
were just trying to find a way of flying it full at the same 
time were promoting our product 
the company inaugurated its sentimental journeys venture on 
thursday whisking press and invited guests on halfhour trips 
around san francisco bay in the twopropeller airplane complete 
with champagne and crew in 1940s style uniforms 
otis spunkmeyer which expects 30 million in sales over the 
next 12 months bought the dc3 for 165000 two months ago 
