<TEXT>
the us dollar fell against most major currencies 
in european trading friday gold prices rose nearly 10 an ounce in 
london and 3 in zurich 
merrill lynch metals specialist ted arnold said gold bullion 
climbed to 43750 bid per troy ounce because of a shortcovering 
rally and a dip in monthly us unemployment figures gold closed 
at 42780 an ounce late thursday 
he said the figures which showed that the february rate fell to 
57 percent from 58 percent in january rekindled fears of 
inflation 
in zurich gold rose less sharply to 432 bid an ounce from 
429 dollars on shortcovering prompted by gains in silver and 
platinum dealers said 
in a short sale traders sell borrowed gold in expectation of 
covering those sales by replacing the gold with new lots bought 
at cheaper prices 
foreign exchange dealers said us unemployment figures briefly 
pushed up the us currency but the improvement in the rate was not 
enough to have a lasting effect on the dollar 
in tokyo the dollar inched lower to a closing 12922 japanese 
yen from 12930 yen in london it fell further to 12895 yen 
