friday by the federal aviation administration from its report on 
the results of a monthlong inspection of minneapolisbased 
northwest airlines 
in the area of operations the inspectors found that 
northwest airlines inc does not provide enough qualified 
dispatchers at each dispatch center to ensure proper operational 
control of each flight anonymous letters phone calls and flight 
crew complaints that dispatcher workloads were excessive and that 
the monitoring of flight progress was untimely were substantiated 
by observations of faa inspectors at both the tokyo and minneapolis 
dispatch centers 
